<a href='http://herbaria4.herb.berkeley.edu/eflora_display.php?tid=367'><h3>View taxon page for Centaurea</h3></a><blockquote><h3></h3>
<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 0 ;"><a href="#FR1'">1.</a><a name="FR1."> </a> Corolla yellow

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#FR2'">2.</a><a name="FR2."> </a> Heads sessile or subsessile, subtended by leaf-like bracts <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=2297">.....&nbsp;C. benedicta</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#FR2.">2'</a><a name="FR2'"> </a> Heads generally peduncled (if not, then subtending bracts reduced)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#FR3'">3.</a><a name="FR3."> </a> Corolla 25&ndash;30 mm <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1947">.....&nbsp;C. sulphurea</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#FR3.">3'</a><a name="FR3'"> </a> Corolla generally 10&ndash;20 mm

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#FR4'">4.</a><a name="FR4."> </a> Central spine of main phyllaries 5&ndash;10 mm, &plusmn; purple <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1934">.....&nbsp;C. melitensis</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#FR4.">4'</a><a name="FR4'"> </a> Central spine of main phyllaries 10&ndash;25 mm, straw-colored <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1946">.....&nbsp;C. solstitialis</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 0 ;"><a href="#FR1.">1'</a><a name="FR1'"> </a> Corolla white to pink, blue, or purple

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#FR5'">5.</a><a name="FR5."> </a> Main phyllaries &plusmn; spine-tipped

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#FR6'">6.</a><a name="FR6."> </a> Main phyllary tip-spine 6&ndash;25 mm

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#FR7'">7.</a><a name="FR7."> </a> Pappus 0 <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1922">.....&nbsp;C. calcitrapa</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#FR7.">7'</a><a name="FR7'"> </a> Pappus present, 0.3&ndash;2.5 mm

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#FR8'">8.</a><a name="FR8."> </a> Involucre body 8&ndash;14 mm diam, widely ovoid <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1931">.....&nbsp;C. iberica</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#FR8.">8'</a><a name="FR8'"> </a> Involucre body 5&ndash;10 mm diam, narrowly ovoid <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=91736">.....&nbsp;C. pouzinii</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#FR6.">6'</a><a name="FR6'"> </a> Main phyllary tip-spine 1&ndash;5 mm

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#FR9'">9.</a><a name="FR9."> </a> Outer flower corollas expanded, &plusmn; ray-like, >> disk flower corollas, 25&ndash;35 mm, pink-purple <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1929">.....&nbsp;C. diluta</a> (2)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#FR9.">9'</a><a name="FR9'"> </a> Outer flower corollas not or barely expanded, = or slightly > disk flower corollas, 7&ndash;13 mm, white to pink or pale purple

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#FR10'">10.</a><a name="FR10."> </a> Involucre 10&ndash;13 mm; disk flower corolla 12&ndash;13 mm <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1928">.....&nbsp;C. diffusa</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#FR10.">10'</a><a name="FR10'"> </a> Involucre 7&ndash;8 mm; disk flower corolla 7&ndash;9 mm <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=87483">.....&nbsp;C. virgata subsp. squarrosa</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#FR5.">5'</a><a name="FR5'"> </a> Main phyllaries not spine-tipped

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#FR11'">11.</a><a name="FR11."> </a> Annual

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#FR12'">12.</a><a name="FR12."> </a> Herbage &plusmn; tomentose; disk flower corolla 10&ndash;15 mm <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1925">.....&nbsp;C. cyanus</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#FR12.">12'</a><a name="FR12'"> </a> Herbage puberulent or &plusmn; glabrous, sometimes thinly cobwebby; disk flower corolla &plusmn; 20 mm <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1929">.....&nbsp;C. diluta</a> (2)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#FR11.">11'</a><a name="FR11'"> </a> Biennial or perennial herb

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#FR13'">13.</a><a name="FR13."> </a> Outer and inner flowers bisexual; corollas all &plusmn; equal <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=91735">.....&nbsp;C. jacea subsp. nigra</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#FR13.">13'</a><a name="FR13'"> </a> Outer flowers sterile, inner flowers bisexual; sterile flower corollas > bisexual flower corollas

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#FR14'">14.</a><a name="FR14."> </a> Herbage densely gray-tomentose <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=1924">.....&nbsp;C. cineraria</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#FR14.">14'</a><a name="FR14'"> </a> Herbage &plusmn; green, sometimes thinly cobwebby

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#FR15'">15.</a><a name="FR15."> </a> Involucre 10&ndash;13 mm <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=81084">.....&nbsp;C. stoebe subsp. micranthos</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#FR15.">15'</a><a name="FR15'"> </a> Involucre 15&ndash;18 mm

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 42 ;"><a href="#FR16'">16.</a><a name="FR16."> </a> Phyllary appendages scarious, light brown, concave, entire to coarsely dentate <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=91734">.....&nbsp;C. jacea subsp. jacea</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 42 ;"><a href="#FR16.">16'</a><a name="FR16'"> </a> Phyllary appendages light to dark brown, flat to &plusmn; concave, coarsely dentate to dissected into fine, wire-like lobes <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=93858">.....&nbsp;C. jacea nothosubsp. pratensis</a></blockquote><P>
